{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:1",
      "text": "But I, brethren, could not address you as spiritual men, but as men of the flesh, as babes in Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:2",
      "text": "I fed you with milk, not solid food; for you were not ready for it; and even yet you are not ready,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:3",
      "text": "for you are still of the flesh. For while there is jealousy and strife among you, are you not of the flesh, and behaving like ordinary men?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:4",
      "text": "For when one says, “I belong to Paul,” and another, “I belong to Apollos,” are you not merely men?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:5",
      "text": "What then is Apollos? What is Paul? Servants through whom you believed, as the Lord assigned to each.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:6",
      "text": "I planted, Apollos watered, but God gave the growth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:7",
      "text": "So neither he who plants nor he who waters is anything, but only God who gives the growth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:8",
      "text": "He who plants and he who waters are equal, and each shall receive his wages according to his labor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:9",
      "text": "For we are God's fellow workers; you are God's field, God's building.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:10",
      "text": "According to the grace of God given to me, like a skilled master builder I laid a foundation, and another man is building upon it. Let each man take care how he builds upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:11",
      "text": "For no other foundation can any one lay than that which is laid, which is Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:12",
      "text": "Now if any one builds on the foundation with gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, straw—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:13",
      "text": "each man's work will become manifest; for the Day will disclose it, because it will be revealed with fire, and the fire will test what sort of work each one has done.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:14",
      "text": "If the work which any man has built on the foundation survives, he will receive a reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:15",
      "text": "If any man's work is burned up, he will suffer loss, though he himself will be saved, but only as through fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:16",
      "text": "Do you not know that you are God's temple and that God's Spirit dwells in you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:17",
      "text": "If any one destroys God's temple, God will destroy him. For God's temple is holy, and that temple you are.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:18",
      "text": "Let no one deceive himself. If any one among you thinks that he is wise in this age, let him become a fool that he may become wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:19",
      "text": "For the wisdom of this world is folly with God. For it is written, “He catches the wise in their craftiness,”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:20",
      "text": "and again, “The Lord knows that the thoughts of the wise are futile.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:21",
      "text": "So let no one boast of men. For all things are yours,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:22",
      "text": "whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas or the world or life or death or the present or the future, all are yours;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.3.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:23",
      "text": "and you are Christ's; and Christ is God's.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
